Small note: phobias are, almost by definition, nonesensical. Being afraid of walking behind of a horse makes sense because it can kick you and harm you. It's fear.

Seeing a picture of a horse or at best seeing one 50 meters away from you and losing your shit is nonesensical. It's a phobia.

I guess that when you say  you mean weird stuff like being afraid of blue paper, for example. But I'm not sure just HOW nonesensical real phobias can get. Simply because the most common ones are fear of spiders and such, that doesnt mean they make sense in the first place, or that truly weird shit doesnt exist. Maybe someone actually has a phobia for blue papers, you know?







